Subject: Re: Getting the lights off the nose

>First, the blinkers are riveted on. Eventually, I broke the plastic
trying to figure out how to get them off (patience really is a virtue).

Rivets can be drilled out by using a drill bit that's about the same
size as the rivet head (or bigger) and slowly drilling on the head. Most
of the time the drill will rip the head off the rivet and you can push
the other part of the rivet through!
